inset-0 z-10"></div><img src="https://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2F52652e63365208885f555c81484ff15eb2155f66-1447x859.jpg&amp;w=3840&amp;q=75" srcSet="https://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2F52652e63365208885f555c81484ff15eb2155f66-1447x859.jpg&w=1920&q=75amp;qhttps://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2F52652e63365208885f555c81484ff15eb2155f66-1447x859.jpg&w=3840&q=75;w=3840&amp;q=75 2x" alt="Bar Design NYC, Bolt, Bolt Builds, Bolt Builds NYC, Bolt Builds New York City, Bolt Design NYC, Bolt New York City, Boutique Design Agency New York, Custom Interior Design New York, Custom millwork NYC, Elegant Hospitality Interiors NYC, High-End Bar Design NYC, High-End Interior Design Agency NYC, High-End Retail Design New York, High-end Millwork NYC, Hospitality, Hospitality Interior Design New York, Innovative Hospitality Solutions New York, Luxery Millwork NYC, Luxury Bar Design NYC, Luxury Hospitality Consultants NYC, Luxury Millwork NYC, NYC Residential Interior Designers, New York, New York City, New York Design and Branding for Hospitality, New York Hospitality Branding, New York Retail Interior Design, Sophisticated Branding Agency NYC, luxury Hospitality Design NYC" width="1447" height="859" class="absolute object-cover w-full h-full z-0 inset-0" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 300vw, (max-width: 1000px) 200vw, 100vw"/></div><div class="border-x flex-1 flex flex-col justify-end"></div></header><div class="z-20 relative bg-white"><div class="sticky top-0 invisible"><div class="px-unit absolute left-0 right-0 bg-white"><div class="pt-unit border-black border-b"></div></div></div><div class="px-unit"><div class="pt-unit border-black border-x"><div class="sticky top-unit"><div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-unit px-unit pt-2 pb-4"><div class="col-span-6 lg:col-span-3 pr-2"><p class="text-current font-body text-3xl">Senior Project Manager </p></div><div class="col-span-6 lg:col-span-2"><h3 class="text-current font-body text-md">February 4, 2026</h3></div></div></div><div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-unit px-unit pt-8 pb-unit"><div class="col-start-1 col-end-13 md:col-start-2 md:col-end-12 lg:col-start-4 lg:col-end-12 xl:col-start-4 xl:col-end-10"><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"><strong>About Us<br/></strong>Bolt Builds is a full-service Design + Build firm and fully insured General Contractor based in Brooklyn. We specialize in design-forward hospitality, retail, and residential projects that merge classical sensibility with innovative construction and fabrication methods. We believe that great design is only as strong as its execution — and that means being just as rigorous about budgets, schedules, and communication as we are about creative vision.</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"><strong>The Role<br/></strong>We’re looking for a Senior Project Manager to lead high-caliber design+build projects from pre-construction through closeout. This is a senior leadership role focused not just on coordination, but true ownership of the budget, the timeline, the client relationship, and the finished product. You’ll serve as the primary point of contact for clients and consultants, guiding them through every stage of the process with clarity and confidence. Internally, you’ll collaborate with our design, construction, and fabrication consultants to ensure seamless execution and mentor junior team members along the way. You’ll be accountable for delivering exceptional projects on time and on budget, while protecting both creative intent and financial integrity.</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"><strong>What You’ll Do</strong></p><ul class="space-y-2"><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4"><strong>Own and manage project budgets </strong>from initial estimating through closeout: tracking costs, flagging risk, ensuring profitability</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Serve as the <strong>primary point of contact </strong>for clients, consultants, and vendors across all phases of the project</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Lead project planning, timeline development, and resource coordination across design and construction teams</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Translate design intent into buildable solutions without compromising creative vision or <strong>financial control</strong></li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Prepare, track, and manage all contracts, change orders, and pay applications</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Interface with permitting and city agencies (DOB, FDNY, LPC)to navigate approvals and inspections</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Collaborate closely with construction leads to monitor site progress, sequencing, and subcontractor performance</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Provide consistent, accurate reporting on project status (scope, schedule, and budget) to clients and internal leadership</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Mentor junior PMs and project coordinators, helping to grow Bolt’s next generation of leaders</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Continuously improve internal workflows, documentation standards, and cost-control systems</li></ul><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"><strong>What We’re Looking For</strong></p><ul class="space-y-2"><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4"><strong>10+ years</strong> of experience managing complex projects, preferably in a design+build or high-end interiors setting</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Proven track record of <strong>owning multi-million-dollar project budgets</strong>, including forecasting, reporting, and financial decision-making</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Strong familiarity with NYC permitting and agency processes (DOB, FDNY, LPC, etc.)</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Comfortable managing multiple concurrent projects from concept through closeout</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Deep understanding of project sequencing, construction detailing, and value engineering</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Proficiency with industry standard software (Adobe, AutoCAD, Bluebeam, Revit, Rhino, Slack, Notion)</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Excellent communication skills and a strong, client-facing presence</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4"><strong>Highly organized, accountable, and proactive in solving problems before they escalate</strong></li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Committed to mentorship and excited to help build a culture of craft, clarity, and excellence</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Degree in Construction Management, Architecture, or a related field required</li></ul><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"><strong>Why Bolt</strong></p><ul class="space-y-2"><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4"><strong>See your work built — and built fast. </strong>At Bolt, you won’t be stuck pushing paper for years before seeing results. Our projects move quickly, and the work you put in becomes something real, tangible, and lasting.</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4"><strong>Be hands-on. </strong>You won’t be siloed behind a screen — you’ll be in the field, in meetings, on walk-throughs, and fully involved in the process from start to finish.</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4"><strong>Work in the heart of Greenpoint. </strong>Our studio is based in one of Brooklyn’s most creative neighborhoods — surrounded by great food, inspiring spaces, and a thriving design community.</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4"><strong>Join a company on the rise. </strong>Bolt is entering a new chapter of growth — and we’re building something special. You’ll help shape the future of the company, not just execute the present.</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4"><strong>Build projects you</strong>’<strong>re proud of. </strong>From thoughtful restaurants to bold retail environments, you’ll be part of a team that sweats the details and cares deeply about design, craft, and execution.</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4"><strong>Work with good people. </strong>We’re a tight-knit, driven team that takes pride in what we do — and has fun doing</li></ul><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"><strong>Compensation</strong></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">This is a full-time, in-person role based in our Greenpoint, Brooklyn studio.</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">The base salary range for this position is <strong>$75,000–$105,000</strong>, depending on experience and qualifications. Bolt also offers performance-based bonus opportunities and clear pathways for professional growth.</p><div class="mt-16 pb-12"><div class="px-6 py-8 bg-faint text-center"><p class="text-current font-body text-xl">To apply for this job, please email your resume to<!-- --> <a href="mailto:hello@bolt.build" class="font-bold hover:text-blue transition-colors border-b border-current border-dotted">hello@bolt.build ↗</a>.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><footer class="bg-white pb-unit px-unit relative z-[1000]"><div class="bg-white border border-b border-black pt-unit pb-unit"><div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-unit px-unit"><div class="col-span-6 lg:col-span-3"><a class="text-current hover:text-yellow transition-colors" href="../index.html"><div class="w-[24px]"><div class="w-full "><svg width="100%" height="100%" viewBox="0 0 114 265" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><title>Bolt Design NYC Logo</titl